    </teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart" subtype="chapter">
                    <ab><title>Deuteronomy 7</title>
                        <milestone unit="line" xml:id="Deut007-P292v-L8_trl" n="8"
                            prev="ADub.III.73.005.006.trl.xml#Deut006-P292v-L8_trl" />
                        <l n="1">And it shall be,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                             if the Lord your God brings you to the land to which you are coming to
                            inherit
                            <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                             it, he will drive many kingdoms before you, the Hittites, and the
                            <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                             Girgashites, and the Amorites, and the Canaanites, and the
                            <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                             Perizzites, and the Hivites, and the Jebusites, seven kingdoms
                            <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                             greater and mightier than you.</l>
                        <l n="2">And
                            <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                             the Lord your God will give them over to you, and you shall strike
                            them,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                             utterly destroy them. You shall make no covenant with them and you
                            shall show no mercy
                            <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                             to them.</l>
                        <l n="3">And you shall not make marriages with them:
                            <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                             you shall not give your daughter to his son, and you shall not take his
                            daughter for your son,</l>
                        <l n="4">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                             Because they will turn away your son from my service and they will
                            <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                             serve other gods, and the anger of the Lord will be kindled against
                            you,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="20" />
                             and he will destroy you quickly.</l>
                        <l n="5">But thus shall you do to them:
                            <milestone unit="line" n="21" />
                             you shall destroy their altars and cut down their pillars and
                            <milestone unit="page" n="293r" />
                            <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                             chop their idol poles and burn their carved idols
                            <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                             in fire.</l>
                        <l n="6">Because you are a holy people to the Lord
                            <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                             your God. The Lord your God has chosen you to be a chosen
                            <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                             people to himself of all the peoples that are on the face of the
                            earth.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                        <l n="7">It was not because of you being more |numerous| than all the
                            peoples
                            <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                             that the Lord loved you so that he chose you, because you are the
                            <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                             fewest of all people.</l>
                        <l n="8">But because of the Lord’s loving
                            <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                             you and because of his keeping the oath
                            <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                             which he had sworn to your fathers, the Lord brought you out with a
                            strong hand
                            <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                             and redeemed you out of the reign of slaves, from the hand of
                            <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                             Pharaoh, king of Egypt.</l>
                        <l n="9">And know that the Lord your God:
                            <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                             he is God, the faithful God who keeps covenant
                            <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                             and mercy with them that love him <seg type="commented"
                                corresp="#Deut-007-seg001_trl" />to read his Law<anchor
                                type="commented" xml:id="Deut-007-seg001_trl" /><ref n="1"
                                target="#Deut-007-fn1_trl" type="noteAnchor" /> and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                             keep his commandments to a thousand generations,</l>
                        <l n="10">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                             And pays back to his enemies <seg type="commented"
                                corresp="#Deut-007-seg002_trl" />while they are |still| alive<anchor
                                type="commented" xml:id="Deut-007-seg002_trl" /><ref n="2"
                                target="#Deut-007-fn2_trl" type="noteAnchor" />
                            <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                             to destroy them. He will not hold back the payment to his enemies,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                             he will repay them <seg type="commented" corresp="#Deut-007-seg003_trl"
                             />while they are alive<anchor type="commented"
                                xml:id="Deut-007-seg003_trl" /><ref n="3" target="#Deut-007-fn3_trl"
                                type="noteAnchor" />.</l>
                        <l n="11">You shall keep the
                            <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                             commandments and the statutes and the judgments
                            <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                             which I command you today, to do them.
                            <milestone unit="line" n="20" />
                            <emph>Parashat Eikev</emph></l>
                        <milestone unit="page" n="293v" />
                        <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                        <l n="12">And it shall be,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                             because, if you listen to these judgments
                            <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                             and keep |them and| do them, then the Lord your God
                            <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                             will keep for you the covenant and the mercy which he swore
                            <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                             to your fathers.</l>
                        <l n="13">And he will love you and bless
                            <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                             you and multiply you. And he will bless the fruit of your womb
                            <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                             and the fruit of your land — your grain and your must and your olive
                            oil,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                             the progeny of your cattle and the females of your sheep —
                            <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                             on the land which he swore to your fathers to give you.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                        <l n="14">You will be more blessed than all the peoples. There will not be
                            <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                             a barren man or barren woman among you or among your cattle.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                        <l n="15">And the Lord will take away from you all sickness, and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                             all the evil diseases of Egypt which you know: he will not put
                            <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                             them on you, but he will lay them on all your enemies.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                        <l n="16">And you will consume all the people whom the Lord
                            <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                             your God is giving you. Your eye shall have no pity on them,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                             and you shall not serve their gods, because it is a snare
                            <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                             to you.</l>
                        <l n="17">If you say in your heart, “These kingdoms are more
                            <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                             than I; how will I be able to destroy them?”.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="20" />
                        <l n="18">You shall not be afraid of them. And you shall remember what
                            <milestone unit="line" n="21" />
                             the Lord your God did to Pharaoh and to all Egypt:</l>
                        <l n="19">
                            <milestone unit="page" n="294r" />
                            <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                             The great trials which your eyes saw and the signs
                            <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                             and the wonders and the strong hand and the
                            <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                             outstretched arm by which the Lord your God brought you out. So will
                            the Lord your God do
                            <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                             to all the people before whom you fear.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                        <l n="20">And the Lord your God will send the hornet
                            <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                             among them as well until those who are left and those who hide
                            themselves
                            <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                             from you, be destroyed from before you.</l>
                        <l n="21">Do not be broken down before them,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                             because the Lord your God is among you, a mighty and awesome God.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                        <l n="22">And the Lord your God will drive out those kingdoms
                            <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                             before you little by little. You will not be able to consume them
                            <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                             at once, lest the wild |animals| of the field will become many at
                            you.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                        <l n="23">And the Lord your God will give them before you and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                             will cause a stir among them with a great confusion, until they are
                            destroyed.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                        <l n="24">And he will give their kings in your hand, and you shall destroy
                            <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                             their name from under the skies.
                            <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                             Not a man will be able to stand before you, until you have destroyed
                            them.</l>
                        <l n="25">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                             You shall burn their carved idols in fire. You shall not desire
                            <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                             the silver or gold that is on them, and you shall not take
                            <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                             it to you, lest you be snared by it, because it is an abomination
                            <milestone unit="line" n="20" />
                             to the Lord your God.</l>
                        <l n="26">And you shall not bring an abominable thing
                            <milestone unit="line" n="21" />
                             to your house, lest you become like a devoted thing. You shall utterly
                            make it abominable,
                            <milestone unit="page" n="294v" />
                            <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                             and you shall utterly despise it, because it is a devoted
                            <milestone unit="line" xml:id="Deut007-P294v-L2_trl" n="2"
                                next="ADub.III.73.005.008.trl.xml#Deut008-P294v-L2_trl" />
                             thing. </l>
                    </ab>
                </div>
